            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="357" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EW1">E.
                    W.</gloss>/6–2545</note>
                <head>No. 357<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Acting Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="1" xml:id="d357fn1">For other
                            extracts from this memorandum, see <ref target="#d99">documents Nos.
                                99</ref>, <ref target="#d616">616</ref>, and <ref target="#d637">637</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-25">June 25,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum of Conversation</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">Subject: United States–French Relations</p>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell rendition="#top #nowrap">Participants:</cell>
                        <cell>The French Ambassador, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BH1">Henri
                                Bonnet</persName>: Acting Secretary, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName>.</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p>The French Ambassador called on me this morning and took up first the request of
                    his Government, presented in the appended <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>,<note n="2" xml:id="d357fn2">Not found.</note> that we
                    instruct our Ambassador in Moscow to keep the French Ambassador<note n="3" xml:id="d357fn3">General of the Army <persName corresp="#p_CGAG1">Georges
                            Catroux</persName>.</note> informed of developments in the work of the
                    tripartite Reparations Commission. The Ambassador pointed out once more the
                    interest of France in the whole subject of reparations and the feeling of his
                    Government that a French representative should have been included in the
                    Commission especially in view of the great sufferings which France had endured
                    during the war. I said to the Ambassador that I would immediately give
                    consideration to his request and that in the meantime he was well aware of the
                    position we had taken that we would like to have France included in the
                    Commission and that our position in principle had not altered.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">J[<hi rend="smallcaps">oseph</hi>] C. G[<hi rend="smallcaps">rew</hi>]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
